In this article, President Barack Obama proclaims April 15 through April 21, 2012, as National Volunteer Week. He highlights the importance of volunteerism in shaping the nation and achieving progress. He acknowledges the countless acts of service that occur throughout the country and mentions the transformative power of service to unite, build, and heal communities. The President emphasizes his administration's commitment to empowering Americans with tools to shape their communities, such as the Edward M. Kennedy Serve America Act and the establishment of the Social Innovation Fund and FEMA Corps. He encourages all Americans to volunteer and make service a part of their daily lives, stating that service not only benefits those in need but also provides valuable skills and opportunities for volunteers. The article concludes with the President's proclamation and a call to action for Americans to participate in service projects.